KLR-70) may serve as orthogonal inhibitors of chaperone binding and translation. In summary, KLR-70 is a novel chaperone inhibitor with high affinity and selectivity for bacterial Hsp70 and with considerable potential to help parsing out the role of Hsp70 in nascent protein folding.

