where IVV and IVH denote the fluorescence intensity following excitation by verticallypolarized light and passing through either a vertical or horizontal emission polarizer, respectively. Similarly, IHV and IHH denote the sample fluorescence intensity following excitation by horizontally polarized light and passing through either a vertical or horizontal emission polarizer, respectively. All intensities were background-subtracted prior to further analysis. The background consisted of an independently-prepared equivalent sample lacking KLR-70-C-AF488. The changes in KLR-70-C-AF488 anisotropy as a function of total DnaK concentration were then plotted and fitted to the expressions below with Origin (OriginLab Corporation, v. 2020). Binding to DnaK was modeled as a simple two-state process (see eqns 4 and 5). Equation 6 can be recast as

