Importantly, no statistically significant changes in total fluorescence intensity of KLR-70-CAF488 were observed in the presence of ADP-DnaK. Therefore Q was taken to be equal 1.0 in our experiments (Figure S3).

Experimental data points were then fit to equation 13, after replacement of equation 12 into it,, with KD2, rfree and rbound as adjustable parameters. Data are reported as an average KD2 from n = 4 independent experiments ± standard error.

Competitive binding experiments.—In order to quantify the affinity of unlabeled KLR-70 for ADP-DnaK, competitive binding experiments were carried out. These experiments were conducted under similar conditions to those employed in the direct binding experiments, except that KLR-70 (1 – 1000 μM) was co-incubated with DnaK (10 μM) and KLR-70-C-AF488 (10 nM) in 50 mM Tris/HCl pH 7.0, 5 mM MgCl2, 50 mM KCl, 5 mM ADP and 15 mM dithiothreitol (DTT) for 1 hr at 21.5 ± 0.5 °C.

