Figure 9. KLR-70 inhibits a significant portion of the chaperone activity of cell-like environments. (A) Normalized luminescence data, illustrating of the extent of luciferase (50 nM) refolding in a cell-like environment (c.f. mix, see components in Methods section) containing either purified K/J/E chaperones (i.e., DnaK, DnaJ and GrpE), or S30 cell extracts from a wild-
type (WT) strain, or S30 extracts from a trigger factor-depleted (Δtig) strain. The total concentration of the purified K/J/E chaperones was: 1.1 μM DnaK, 0.2 μM DnaJ and 0.5 μM GrpE, respectively. KLR-70 was 400 μM in the experiments that included it. Bar-graph colors denote refolding in the absence (black) or presence of E. coli S30 extracts (dark grey: WT; light grey: Δtig). (B) Alternative plot of the data of panel A, showing relative normalized relative luminescence values. All data represent avg ± std. err. for n = 3 independent experiments.
Biochemistry. Author manuscript; available in PMC 2021 July 30.

